name: 16S rRNA pseudouridine516 synthase
comment: The enzyme is specific for uridine516 in 16S rRNA. In vitro, the enzyme does not modify free 16S rRNA. The preferred substrate is a 5'-terminal fragment of 16S rRNA complexed with 30S ribosomal proteins [1].
